STONY CREEK WIND FARM, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Stony Creek Wind Farm, LLC ("Stony Creek") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Stony Creek generating facility ("Stony Creek Facility").
The Stony Creek Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Somerset County, Pennsylvania. The Stony Creek Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Mid-Atlantic Interstate Transmission, LLC and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Stony Creek's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Stony Creek Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Stony Creek's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Stony Creek shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $208,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $17,333.33.
